-- Credit Suisse Investment Bank Chairman Paul Calello Has Died
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   H a r p e r
-- 2010-11-16T16:44:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-16/credit-suisse-investment-bank-chairman-paul-calello-dead-of-cancer-at-49.html
     Nov. 16 (Bloomberg) -- Paul Calello , the chairman of the
investment banking business at  Credit Suisse Group AG , has died,
the firm said today in a statement.  Calello, 49, had been battling cancer.  “Paul Calello was an outstanding leader, and a down-to-
earth, very human colleague who forged strong relationships and
made a positive difference in the world around him,’’ Brady Dougan , the chief executive officer of the Swiss bank, said in
the statement. “We will miss him greatly, but his spirit and
accomplishments will remain a part of Credit Suisse. Our
thoughts are with his family today.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christine Harper in New York at 
